hopobject.body: Other amount ostarine mk-2866 cycle It is clear that, aside from institutions that must be bailed out if they get into trouble, the concentration of banking activity into a handful of institutions has created an oligopoly that is empowered to parasitically extract value from the rest of the economy in dangerous amounts. The financial sector share of GDP has doubled in the last 30 years. In other words, the financial sector has not just done well; it has completely outpaced the rest of the productive sectors.
